Pico 7 fire panel firmware.

Buttons:
- GP2: status
- GP3: film-on
- GP4: film-off
- GP5: sound-look
- GP6: sound-crash
- GP7: sound-fail
- GP8: sound-pass
- GP9: sound-bake
- GP10: unlock
- GP11: reset-all, hold for 5 seconds

Each button connects GPIO to GND. Internal pull-ups are enabled.

Status LEDs:
- G1/R1: film
- G2/R2: sound
- G3/R3: picture
- G4/R4: buttons
- G5/R5: potentiometer / Raspberry Pi

The panel publishes escape/fire/... button events and subscribes to
escape/cmd/fire-panel/led for LED state updates.

Reset safety:
- Hold GP11 for 5 seconds.
- The five red LEDs flash one at a time as a countdown.
- After the hold completes, all five red LEDs flash together.
- The panel publishes escape/fire/reset-all, then starts the status sequence.
